1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 5=

3
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:20,980
Honey, you're back.

4
00:02:32,450 --> 00:02:33,290
I'm back.

5
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:35,980
I didn't eat lunch. I'm starving.

6
00:02:35,980 --> 00:02:36,850
Let's eat together.

7
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:38,690
I already ate. I'm not hungry.

8
00:02:39,570 --> 00:02:40,410
It's already made.

9
00:02:40,690 --> 00:02:41,530
Have some.

10
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:05,940
Don't turn around.

11
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:08,450
I think she saw us.

12
00:03:16,410 --> 00:03:17,250
Does it taste a bit plain?

13
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:19,570
The flavor is just right.

14
00:03:21,540 --> 00:03:22,380
It's okay.

15
00:03:38,570 --> 00:03:39,410
Yu,

16
00:03:41,450 --> 00:03:42,450
didn't go out tonight?

17
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:45,100
I've been working
at home all along. What's up?

18
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:47,380
Nothing.

19
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:55,690
Did you come back from the music store?

20
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:56,940
Yeah, why?

21
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:03,340
I went to the music store
in the evening.

22
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,060
You weren't there.

23
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:08,730
If you go back this late,
will she get angry?

24
00:04:09,010 --> 00:04:10,410
She should be asleep by now.

25
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:11,540
Besides,

26
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:13,170
we haven't really talked in ages.

27
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:14,970
Where did you go?

28
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:19,900
What are you really doing?

29
00:04:20,610 --> 00:04:22,340
The music store had
no income this month again.

30
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:23,980
I'll have to cover
the rent for you again.

31
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:28,410
I went out to eat with Gong and Bei.

32
00:04:28,770 --> 00:04:30,450
I didn't tell you
because I was afraid you'd be unhappy.

33
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:32,020
Why would I be unhappy?

34
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:36,020
Don't you always say
they're my bad friends?

35
00:04:36,170 --> 00:04:37,490
Am I wrong?

36
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:39,580
I've been working, always busy.

37
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:40,460
And what about you?

38
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:42,430
Hanging out with a group of people,
not focusing on proper work.

39
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:43,580
What do you mean?

40
00:04:43,810 --> 00:04:45,340
Making music is
my proper work, isn't it?

41
00:04:45,460 --> 00:04:46,730
Did I stop you from making music?

42
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:48,730
Even if it doesn't make money,

43
00:04:48,730 --> 00:04:49,980
I still let you open this music store,

44
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,170
just so you'd have a place

45
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:52,410
to write songs properly.

46
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:53,700
I don't want to argue with you.

47
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,460
Neither do I.

48
00:05:10,490 --> 00:05:12,250
Remember how long it's been
since you called me "honey"?

49
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:16,130
Honey,

50
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,850
let's get a dog someday.

51
00:05:18,170 --> 00:05:19,010
Sure.

52
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,610
A corgi or a beagle?

53
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:21,990
How about a French bulldog?

54
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:25,490
French bulldogs are too ugly.

55
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:26,370
Is it?

56
00:05:29,170 --> 00:05:30,010
No, not really.

57
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:32,730
As long as you like it, it's not ugly.

58
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:35,340
Let's give it a name.

59
00:05:35,780 --> 00:05:36,620
How about...

60
00:05:36,850 --> 00:05:38,580
Unicorn?

61
00:05:38,930 --> 00:05:39,770
Why?

62
00:05:39,930 --> 00:05:41,780
Loyal and steadfast, you said it.

63
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:44,730
In the future,

64
00:05:45,170 --> 00:05:46,010
you'd hold me close.

65
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:47,780
And I'd hug the dog.

66
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,700
We'd watch movies together,

67
00:05:49,930 --> 00:05:52,100
talking about our day.

68
00:05:52,370 --> 00:05:55,780
Then it's just our private world.

69
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:58,140
You're so annoying.

70
00:05:59,410 --> 00:06:01,170
What are you thinking about?

71
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:06,100
When we first got together,

72
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,610
we called each other
all those sweet names,

73
00:06:11,930 --> 00:06:13,100
but

74
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:16,020
why have we become like strangers?

75
00:06:16,930 --> 00:06:18,730
What's the point
for an old married couple?

76
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:19,690
It's so cheesy.

77
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:21,860
Cheesy, huh?

78
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:24,330
Yeah, maybe.

79
00:06:27,290 --> 00:06:28,490
I'm no longer

80
00:06:30,460 --> 00:06:32,370
the young girl in your eyes anymore.

81
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,700
Calling a woman like me "honey"

82
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:36,250
must be embarrassing for you.

83
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:41,100
Fine, I'll say it now.

84
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:42,330
Honey.

85
00:06:42,850 --> 00:06:43,690
Is that enough?

86
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:45,100
Are you trying to insult me?

87
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:46,490
No, what do you really want?

88
00:06:46,980 --> 00:06:48,250
Can you stop stirring up trouble?

89
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:49,780
Every day, you come up with
all kinds of reasons

90
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,020
to argue with me. Is it fun?

91
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:04,020
I really don't want to argue.

92
00:07:06,780 --> 00:07:07,780
I just don't know

93
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,050
how the two of us ended up

94
00:07:10,050 --> 00:07:11,250
like this.

95
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:13,730
Where did we go wrong?

96
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:28,370
If you have nothing to say, let's sleep.

97
00:07:29,290 --> 00:07:30,540
I know you're tired. Get some rest.

98
00:07:45,980 --> 00:07:47,780
What are you doing now? Working?

99
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:50,660
I opened a flower shop.

100
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:52,490
A flower shop? That's nice.

101
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:53,500
It suits a girl.

102
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,540
I also invested in a coffee shop

103
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:56,770
and a women's club.

104
00:07:58,580 --> 00:08:00,410
Can I change and call you

105
00:08:00,410 --> 00:08:01,340
"Boss Jiang" now?

106
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:03,900
Too late for that, Mr. Gong.

107
00:08:14,050 --> 00:08:15,220
When did you meet Bei?

108
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:17,610
We have known each other
since we were in diapers.

109
00:08:17,610 --> 00:08:18,690
It's been almost over ten years.

110
00:08:20,290 --> 00:08:21,250
Just kidding.

111
00:08:21,850 --> 00:08:23,220
We're from the same hometown.

112
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:25,290
We lived in
the same neighborhood as kids.

113
00:08:25,930 --> 00:08:28,810
How did we end up together?

114
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:30,020
Honestly, I can't even remember.

115
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:33,420
But he wasn't in diapers at the time.

116
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:37,700
Then you must know

117
00:08:39,650 --> 00:08:40,890
how many girlfriends he has had.

118
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:42,730
About...

119
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:46,330
Just one.

120
00:08:47,770 --> 00:08:48,940
We met her a few times together.

121
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:50,980
I thought they'd get married.

122
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:52,820
But just a few years after graduation,

123
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:53,820
they broke up.

124
00:08:57,730 --> 00:08:58,570
So,

125
00:09:00,010 --> 00:09:00,940
was she pretty?

126
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:02,890
Not as pretty as you.

127
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:04,340
She's way below your league.

128
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:05,490
Except she's taller than you.

129
00:09:05,850 --> 00:09:06,940
She has a better figure than you,

130
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,420
and her eyes are bigger than yours.

131
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:11,580
No way.

132
00:09:11,580 --> 00:09:12,580
She's really not pretty.

133
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:17,250
Then why did they break up?

134
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:19,250
Are you done?

135
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,060
Come on, just tell me.

136
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:24,890
Sometimes I think that

137
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,130
what opposes loyalty is never betrayal,

138
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:29,490
but hypocrisy.

139
00:09:31,820 --> 00:09:32,850
What are you trying to say?

140
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,490
The funny thing is

141
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:37,730
that we all live hypocritically.

142
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:40,650
How so?

143
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:46,100
Why don't you tell Bei everything

144
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:47,300
about yourself?

145
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:20,610
Bowie!

146
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:23,300
Bowie, guess who's back?

147
00:10:25,130 --> 00:10:27,850
Is it like a reunion
after a long separation every day?

148
00:10:28,370 --> 00:10:29,250
I'll get your food.

149
00:10:32,580 --> 00:10:33,420
Come on.

150
00:10:33,890 --> 00:10:36,940
Dad will be joining us soon.

151
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,850
He'll play with you every day.

152
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:41,180
Sounds good?

153
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:46,140
Are you asleep?

154
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,690
Yeah, what's up?

155
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:06,370
Ugh, I'm still busy.

156
00:11:06,980 --> 00:11:08,650
Now the whole family depends on me.

157
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:11,010
Before touching me,
think about whether you can afford it.

158
00:11:17,890 --> 00:11:19,130
I'm tired. Let's try it another day.

159
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:29,730
I'm going to the bathroom.

160
00:11:55,820 --> 00:11:57,250
(Not noticed. Don't worry.)

161
00:12:15,850 --> 00:12:18,980
If a relationship is doomed
from the start,

162
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:21,180
would you choose not to love

163
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:22,770
or just love for
as long as each day lasts?

164
00:12:24,460 --> 00:12:26,220
I wouldn't date someone
if I knew there was no future.

165
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:29,460
Do you know how low the probability is

166
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:32,060
to meet someone
who truly shares your values?

167
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:36,130
Are you talking about Jiang Yifan?

168
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:40,980
You love Jiang Yifan.

169
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:42,700
That's not the real me.

170
00:12:43,420 --> 00:12:45,100
Then, between Bei and me,

171
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,650
which version of you is the real one?

172
00:12:54,770 --> 00:12:56,630
Xiaoxi, I bought that
sakura-flavored chocolate

173
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:57,490
you like.

174
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,380
I'm at your place.

175
00:12:58,770 --> 00:12:59,940
Bei went to my place.

176
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:01,890
I'll call him.

177
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:11,090
Hello.

178
00:13:12,820 --> 00:13:13,850
Where are you?

179
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:16,370
I'm out having a late-night snack.

180
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:18,610
I thought you were asleep.

181
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:20,060
No,

182
00:13:20,610 --> 00:13:22,250
I couldn't sleep,
so I came out for a drink.

183
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:24,700
Who are you with?

184
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:25,540
With a friend.

185
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:27,420
Which friend?

186
00:13:27,770 --> 00:13:28,820
Why are you asking so much?

187
00:13:29,730 --> 00:13:30,570
Thanks.

188
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:33,260
Just got here.

189
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,250
Where are you? I'll pick you up.

190
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:40,490
No need, I'll head back on my own later.

191
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:42,580
Sen, I don't want to hurt you.

192
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:43,820
I've said it clearly enough.

193
00:13:43,820 --> 00:13:45,370
We're good friends, so we...

194
00:13:45,370 --> 00:13:46,210
Hey, don't.

195
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:47,250
I won't ask.

196
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,890
It's just that I...

197
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,140
I really want to see you.

198
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:53,370
I'll be back soon.

199
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:54,980
Let's talk tomorrow.

200
00:13:55,650 --> 00:13:57,340
I just bought

201
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,580
your favorite sakura-flavored chocolate.

202
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:01,130
I was worried

203
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:02,370
you might've fallen asleep.

204
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:03,730
So I hung it on the doorknob.

205
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:04,890
When you get back, remember

206
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:06,330
to put it in the fridge.

207
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:08,770
Thanks.

208
00:14:09,530 --> 00:14:10,980
Okay. When you get home,

209
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,180
send me a message, okay?

210
00:14:13,130 --> 00:14:13,980
Yeah.

211
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:14,820
You too.

212
00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:16,700
Get some rest early.

213
00:14:17,610 --> 00:14:18,450
Okay.

214
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:20,540
Bei.

215
00:14:21,340 --> 00:14:22,900
Yeah? What's up?

216
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:24,940
I love you.

217
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,090
Love you too.

218
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:36,060
Then... go to bed early, okay?

219
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:37,940
Yeah.

220
00:14:37,940 --> 00:14:38,780
Mingming...

221
00:14:40,370 --> 00:14:41,300
I...

222
00:14:41,530 --> 00:14:42,370
Bye.

223
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,140
I love you.

224
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:58,980
Which admirer was that?

225
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:04,610
What's wrong?

226
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:06,370
Are you jealous?

227
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:10,850
Go ahead.

228
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:13,370
It's getting late.

229
00:15:14,370 --> 00:15:15,210
I should head back.

230
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:16,340
Let me walk you.

231
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:17,980
Better not.

232
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:20,420
Since you can't stay with me all night,

233
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:21,980
let me walk you this once.

234
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,090
Let's go.

235
00:15:44,730 --> 00:15:45,890
Why aren't you sleeping?

236
00:15:58,420 --> 00:16:01,010
♪I admit it♪

237
00:16:01,020 --> 00:16:05,050
♪My back is against the wall♪

238
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:09,450
♪There's nothing I wouldn't try to do♪

239
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:14,010
♪I resist♪

240
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:18,400
♪Your gaze, your lips♪

241
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:21,010
♪Your touch is a gift♪

242
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:25,250
♪There's no one that
I wouldn't try to fool♪

243
00:16:25,260 --> 00:16:28,930
♪For an image of you♪

244
00:16:29,940 --> 00:16:32,370
♪Take my hand again♪

245
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:34,130
♪Take my mind again♪

246
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:37,570
♪Break it to my heart again♪

247
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:39,890
♪I'm falling down again♪

248
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:42,010
♪I'm on my knees again♪

249
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:45,850
♪To beg for the truth♪

250
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:51,480
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

251
00:16:51,490 --> 00:16:56,850
♪Is that the secret of love♪

252
00:16:57,030 --> 00:17:00,050
♪I thought I had kept it from below♪

253
00:17:00,070 --> 00:17:03,410
♪Did it come from above♪

254
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:07,240
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

255
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:12,810
♪Is that the secret of love♪

256
00:17:12,970 --> 00:17:15,650
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing♪

257
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:20,090
♪This secret of love♪

258
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:21,940
Mingming!

259
00:17:23,730 --> 00:17:25,090
Mingming...

260
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:31,670
♪In every corner of the room♪

261
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:35,990
♪There's your lingering shadow♪

262
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,070
♪When night falls♪

263
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:40,110
♪I still love you♪

264
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:43,300
♪More intoxicated, more deeply♪

265
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,950
♪Even if oceans dry and rocks crumble♪

266
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,820
♪I'll still hold you♪

267
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:51,500
♪Only you make me feel truly alive♪

268
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:55,550
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

269
00:17:55,560 --> 00:18:00,800
♪Is that the secret of love♪

270
00:18:00,810 --> 00:18:04,060
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing♪

271
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:08,660
♪This secret of love♪

272
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:12,840
♪No need to argue anymore♪

273
00:18:13,350 --> 00:18:17,170
♪No need for more lies, one by one♪

274
00:18:17,450 --> 00:18:24,950
♪There's nowhere left to hide♪

275
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:08,260
(Liang)

276
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,570
- Morning.
- Morning, Xiaoxi.

277
00:20:12,620 --> 00:20:14,140
Fresh out of the oven.

278
00:20:14,570 --> 00:20:15,460
Thanks.

279
00:20:15,660 --> 00:20:16,770
Look what I brought you.

280
00:20:17,010 --> 00:20:18,700
Wow, this is expensive.

281
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:19,980
Why did you buy so much?

282
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:22,570
He bought them, knowing I love these.

283
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:24,330
Oh,

284
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:26,090
he looks kinda clueless.

285
00:20:26,290 --> 00:20:27,810
I didn't expect him to be so thoughtful.

286
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:33,010
That's not what I meant.

287
00:20:33,290 --> 00:20:34,140
I mean...

288
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:36,380
Bei is wise but appears simple-minded.

289
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:38,220
Gentle and refined,
like a modest gentleman.

290
00:20:41,940 --> 00:20:43,140
Honestly, I can't figure him out.

291
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:43,980
Usually, he's so quiet.

292
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:46,010
But sometimes, when he does things...

293
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:48,140
it's really unexpected.

294
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:51,140
Why is this chocolate so tangy?

295
00:20:53,180 --> 00:20:55,140
Turns out it's because of your talk.

296
00:20:57,770 --> 00:20:58,900
Hello, welcome.

297
00:21:02,810 --> 00:21:04,140
Do you have any nice roses?

298
00:21:04,230 --> 00:21:05,090
It's for my girlfriend.

299
00:21:05,090 --> 00:21:06,620
We have a wide variety of roses here.

300
00:21:11,090 --> 00:21:12,090
Take a look at this one.

301
00:21:12,090 --> 00:21:13,770
This one's called "Intimate Lover".
What do you think?

302
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:15,010
Is this preserved?

303
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:16,060
I don't know much.

304
00:21:16,330 --> 00:21:17,180
No, it's not.

305
00:21:17,180 --> 00:21:18,570
For preserved flowers,
they're over here.

306
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:20,900
Take a look at this one.

307
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:22,090
"Companions Through Life".

308
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:23,700
Many young ladies like it.

309
00:21:24,010 --> 00:21:24,850
And this one,

310
00:21:25,010 --> 00:21:26,010
"Romeo's Poem".

311
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:27,020
It's also a top seller.

312
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:28,060
What's this one?

313
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:29,900
You've got great taste.

314
00:21:30,220 --> 00:21:31,570
This is our latest design.

315
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:33,570
It's called "Loving Only You Forever".

316
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:35,300
I'll take this one.

317
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,530
Please prepare three sets for me.

318
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:39,420
You want three of these, right?

319
00:21:39,660 --> 00:21:40,500
Yeah.

320
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:57,780
Bei.

321
00:21:58,330 --> 00:21:59,170
Come in.

322
00:21:59,780 --> 00:22:00,620
Bei,

323
00:22:00,620 --> 00:22:02,290
a customer has a dispute
about the appraisal result.

324
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:03,500
Could you take a look?

325
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:05,570
Ah, okay.

326
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:06,810
What do you mean by that?

327
00:22:06,980 --> 00:22:08,980
Are you saying my boyfriend
tricked me with a fake bag?

328
00:22:09,140 --> 00:22:10,050
Hey, listen to me.

329
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:11,570
You'd better watch what you say.

330
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,570
- What do you mean?
- I...

331
00:22:13,570 --> 00:22:15,290
Hello, I'm the owner here.

332
00:22:15,770 --> 00:22:16,610
Bei...

333
00:22:17,570 --> 00:22:18,940
Mind if I take a look at the bag?

334
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:19,980
Perfect, the boss is here.

335
00:22:20,090 --> 00:22:21,180
Hurry up and check it.

336
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:23,700
- How could my bag be fake?
- Okay...

337
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:25,330
Are your staff even qualified?

338
00:22:40,140 --> 00:22:41,380
This bag of yours

339
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:44,180
looks almost identical to the real one,

340
00:22:45,090 --> 00:22:46,250
but it's definitely a replica.

341
00:22:47,810 --> 00:22:50,220
My boyfriend said he bought it
at an overseas boutique.

342
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:52,460
How could it possibly be fake?

343
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:54,490
I suspect

344
00:22:54,770 --> 00:22:57,330
he must've used a dishonest agent
and got tricked.

345
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,570
I once accidentally

346
00:22:59,730 --> 00:23:01,010
gave a friend a fake bag.

347
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:03,290
I felt ashamed and angry.

348
00:23:03,620 --> 00:23:04,770
Luckily, my friend believed me.

349
00:23:05,660 --> 00:23:06,620
Otherwise,

350
00:23:06,770 --> 00:23:07,770
it's really hard to explain.

351
00:23:07,770 --> 00:23:09,180
(Zhen Guan)

352
00:23:09,180 --> 00:23:10,020
Here.

353
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:13,860
Alright, when new arrivals come in,

354
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:14,770
I'll let you know right away.

355
00:23:14,770 --> 00:23:15,980
Deal, you said it.

356
00:23:15,990 --> 00:23:16,860
Of course.

357
00:23:16,860 --> 00:23:18,770
Thanks for your hard work today.
Thank you, boss.

358
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:20,090
- Alright, take care.
- Bye.

359
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:20,930
Bye.

360
00:23:25,770 --> 00:23:27,420
Oh, thank goodness
you came to handle it, Bei.

361
00:23:27,570 --> 00:23:29,620
Otherwise, it's really hard
to explain to this kind of customer.

362
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:33,180
But why didn't you
say it straight out earlier?

363
00:23:33,570 --> 00:23:35,460
Even our interns could tell at a glance.

364
00:23:35,620 --> 00:23:37,050
The stitching
and heat stamping on her bag...

365
00:23:37,050 --> 00:23:38,700
It wasn't even a super A-grade fake.

366
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:39,940
A few hundred yuan thing.

367
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:41,250
Where did her boyfriend get it?

368
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:42,860
Could she not tell?

369
00:23:44,570 --> 00:23:46,090
We may be
in the authentication business,

370
00:23:46,860 --> 00:23:47,700
but still,

371
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:49,490
we have to consider
the customer's feelings.

372
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:52,620
She's already suffered financially.

373
00:23:53,010 --> 00:23:54,980
We shouldn't make it worse emotionally.

374
00:23:56,730 --> 00:23:58,180
If someone has to face

375
00:23:58,490 --> 00:23:59,770
a bad outcome,

376
00:24:00,330 --> 00:24:01,460
let's be gentle about it.

377
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:05,090
Hey, Bei,

378
00:24:05,490 --> 00:24:06,450
it seems like there's someone

379
00:24:06,460 --> 00:24:07,730
who's waiting for your gentle side.

380
00:24:09,140 --> 00:24:09,980
Yeah?

381
00:24:13,380 --> 00:24:14,220
Xiaoxi?

382
00:24:14,730 --> 00:24:15,810
When did you get here?

383
00:24:19,050 --> 00:24:20,860
I'm guest-starring
as a flower delivery person today.

384
00:24:21,570 --> 00:24:22,620
I came by to visit.

385
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:24,940
You could've told me you were coming.

386
00:24:25,730 --> 00:24:26,570
Mingming!

387
00:24:26,770 --> 00:24:27,610
Xiaoxi.

388
00:24:27,810 --> 00:24:28,650
These flowers are for you.

389
00:24:28,980 --> 00:24:29,820
For me?

390
00:24:30,530 --> 00:24:32,530
There's a card inside.
Remember to read it.

391
00:24:32,730 --> 00:24:33,620
Thanks, Xiaoxi.

392
00:24:34,490 --> 00:24:35,620
That girl at the table to your left...

393
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:36,940
Her bag

394
00:24:36,940 --> 00:24:38,140
is a pearl chain mini,

395
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:40,940
worth around 50,000 to 60,000.

396
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:42,530
And the one behind you...

397
00:24:43,010 --> 00:24:45,180
That's a classic, and rare leather.

398
00:24:45,570 --> 00:24:47,010
You could buy a small car
for that price.

399
00:24:48,660 --> 00:24:49,770
See the table by the door?

400
00:24:50,290 --> 00:24:51,180
That bag

401
00:24:51,180 --> 00:24:52,460
is around 3,000 to 5,000.

402
00:24:52,660 --> 00:24:54,530
But it's hard to get. It takes a year

403
00:24:55,010 --> 00:24:55,850
to be in stock.

404
00:25:00,570 --> 00:25:02,090
Those two girls who just walked by...

405
00:25:03,050 --> 00:25:04,050
That bag

406
00:25:05,620 --> 00:25:06,510
doesn't look quite genuine.

407
00:25:08,770 --> 00:25:10,010
You're amazing.

408
00:25:10,130 --> 00:25:11,010
Occupational habit.

409
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:12,250
And it's one

410
00:25:12,660 --> 00:25:13,730
of my livelihood skills.

411
00:25:14,140 --> 00:25:14,980
Oh, right.

412
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:15,860
Yeah.

413
00:25:15,860 --> 00:25:17,730
That girl who came
to authenticate the fake bag today...

414
00:25:18,810 --> 00:25:20,570
Do you think her boyfriend
genuinely didn't know?

415
00:25:22,220 --> 00:25:23,460
That's impossible to know.

416
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:26,250
But the fact that
she came for authentication

417
00:25:26,940 --> 00:25:28,530
means she suspects more
than just the bag.

418
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:33,900
And the fact proved that
her suspicion was right.

419
00:25:34,620 --> 00:25:36,420
It's better than
being trapped in a false love,

420
00:25:38,050 --> 00:25:38,980
like...

421
00:25:43,620 --> 00:25:45,700
Do Luanluan and Xiu

422
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:47,460
make you uncomfortable?

423
00:25:48,530 --> 00:25:50,140
How can friends be that close?

424
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:52,700
Don't you have an opinion?

425
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:54,420
Whatever their relationship is,

426
00:25:54,730 --> 00:25:55,900
to us,

427
00:25:56,770 --> 00:25:57,770
they are both our good friends.

428
00:25:58,570 --> 00:25:59,420
If you don't know what to do,

429
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:00,770
make a clean break fast.

430
00:26:01,180 --> 00:26:02,420
End it early.

431
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:04,490
What if I can't?

432
00:26:05,330 --> 00:26:06,700
I don't want to hurt anyone.

433
00:26:07,090 --> 00:26:08,700
But you're already hurting people now.

434
00:26:09,180 --> 00:26:10,140
If you truly like one,

435
00:26:10,250 --> 00:26:11,420
you wouldn't fall for another.

436
00:26:11,620 --> 00:26:13,010
So hurry up and make your choice.

437
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:14,490
Pick the one you truly like.

438
00:26:14,860 --> 00:26:15,700
It's better for everyone.

439
00:26:16,380 --> 00:26:18,620
Yu said Cancer signs

440
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:20,730
are the worst at choosing,

441
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:23,730
and my ascendant is Libra.

442
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:25,570
Luanluan says that makes me indecisive.

443
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:27,570
Useless, a choice wreck.

444
00:26:28,180 --> 00:26:29,020
I'm doomed.

445
00:26:29,570 --> 00:26:30,410
If you don't choose...

446
00:26:31,460 --> 00:26:32,460
So you're planning...

447
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:33,810
To see who drops out first?

448
00:26:35,220 --> 00:26:36,060
Yeah.

449
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:37,940
No matter who gives up on Xiu,

450
00:26:39,490 --> 00:26:40,380
I think

451
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:42,420
Xiu might feel less guilty that way.

452
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:46,330
That's way too sneaky.

453
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:48,460
It's a classic way
to shirk responsibility.

454
00:27:03,010 --> 00:27:04,220
What's wrong? Who's calling?

455
00:27:05,010 --> 00:27:05,850
Nothing.

456
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:07,530
Just an annoying person.

457
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:09,460
Annoying person?

458
00:27:10,050 --> 00:27:11,810
Yeah, anyone who bothers us is annoying.

459
00:27:18,460 --> 00:27:20,010
Last night, you...

460
00:27:23,810 --> 00:27:24,660
Long time no see!

461
00:27:24,660 --> 00:27:25,510
Long time no see.

462
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,530
My girlfriend's a bit shy.

463
00:27:27,530 --> 00:27:29,180
How could I possibly
let the person I love

464
00:27:29,490 --> 00:27:31,940
suffer and cry alongside my buddy?

465
00:27:33,490 --> 00:27:35,660
If Bei really breaks up with you

466
00:27:35,660 --> 00:27:36,810
over this,

467
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:39,620
you can come find me.

468
00:27:42,220 --> 00:27:43,060
I mean,

469
00:27:43,180 --> 00:27:45,460
if you ever want
to go for a walk at night

470
00:27:45,570 --> 00:27:46,570
or grab a drink,

471
00:27:47,290 --> 00:27:48,250
you can call me.

472
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:49,740
After all,

473
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:50,980
it's unsafe alone.

474
00:27:55,620 --> 00:27:57,380
Actually, I wasn't alone last night.

475
00:28:01,330 --> 00:28:03,090
My friend was feeling down.
I was keeping him company.

476
00:28:07,660 --> 00:28:09,140
When will you
introduce this friend to me?

477
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:10,380
I'll treat him to something nice.

478
00:28:11,090 --> 00:28:12,700
Better not.
I'm afraid he might scare you.

479
00:28:13,090 --> 00:28:13,930
Scare me?

480
00:28:14,090 --> 00:28:16,010
Is he or she a female version of Gong?

481
00:28:16,620 --> 00:28:17,700
Pretty much.

482
00:28:19,010 --> 00:28:19,980
Bei?

483
00:28:21,250 --> 00:28:22,250
Yu He?

484
00:28:22,530 --> 00:28:23,380
What a coincidence.

485
00:28:23,380 --> 00:28:24,420
Yeah, long time no see.

486
00:28:24,530 --> 00:28:26,220
Yeah, it's been a year, hasn't it?

487
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:27,730
Hello, I'm Yu He.

488
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:28,900
You changed your hairstyle.

489
00:28:29,010 --> 00:28:30,090
I almost didn't recognize you.

490
00:28:30,730 --> 00:28:33,140
No matter what it takes, this time,

491
00:28:33,530 --> 00:28:34,810
I want to catch him in the act.

492
00:28:36,850 --> 00:28:37,770
Come on, let me introduce you.

493
00:28:37,770 --> 00:28:38,860
Well, Xiaoxi...

494
00:28:39,090 --> 00:28:39,930
Xiaoxi.

495
00:28:40,220 --> 00:28:41,420
Come on, let me introduce you.

496
00:28:41,980 --> 00:28:42,860
- This is...
- Yu He,

497
00:28:45,860 --> 00:28:46,700
long time no see.

498
00:28:49,460 --> 00:28:50,460
I'm Jiang Yifan.

499
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:54,620
Oh, you two know each other?

500
00:28:55,330 --> 00:28:57,620
Yeah, Yu He used
to visit my flower shop often.

501
00:28:57,620 --> 00:28:58,730
We got along well.

502
00:28:59,860 --> 00:29:00,900
How did you two meet?

503
00:29:03,330 --> 00:29:04,490
Through Gong.

504
00:29:04,980 --> 00:29:05,820
Yu He.

505
00:29:08,530 --> 00:29:10,250
Small world, huh?

506
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:12,090
Didn't expect you
to be with a comic artist.

507
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:15,900
It's fine. That's all in the past.

508
00:29:16,010 --> 00:29:16,980
This is my boyfriend.

509
00:29:17,420 --> 00:29:18,290
- Hello.
- Hello.

510
00:29:18,770 --> 00:29:19,700
Hello.

511
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:20,810
I know all about that.

512
00:29:21,050 --> 00:29:22,810
There are no secrets
between Yu He and me.

513
00:29:28,180 --> 00:29:29,980
You even called to invite me out before.

514
00:29:30,290 --> 00:29:31,420
I wondered why you vanished.

515
00:29:31,420 --> 00:29:32,770
Turns out you were dating someone.

516
00:29:33,810 --> 00:29:35,380
I really was busy before.

517
00:29:36,090 --> 00:29:37,620
You and Bei... Are you two...?

518
00:29:37,620 --> 00:29:38,530
We're seeing each other.

519
00:29:41,290 --> 00:29:42,180
It's been three months now.

520
00:29:44,810 --> 00:29:45,650
Never thought

521
00:29:45,900 --> 00:29:47,050
that would happen.

522
00:29:47,250 --> 00:29:48,330
Why is that surprising?

523
00:29:49,290 --> 00:29:50,290
That's right.

524
00:29:50,900 --> 00:29:52,330
Why didn't you introduce us sooner?

525
00:29:52,570 --> 00:29:53,410
Exactly.

526
00:29:54,050 --> 00:29:54,900
How would I know

527
00:29:55,180 --> 00:29:56,330
you were into this type?

528
00:30:01,490 --> 00:30:02,700
Want to sit and chat for a bit?

529
00:30:02,940 --> 00:30:04,140
No need. We're done eating.

530
00:30:04,250 --> 00:30:05,090
You carry on.

531
00:30:05,090 --> 00:30:06,180
Alright.

532
00:30:06,330 --> 00:30:07,730
Well, let's catch up later.

533
00:30:08,900 --> 00:30:10,090
Without inviting... you know who,

534
00:30:10,090 --> 00:30:10,980
we'll hang out.

535
00:30:11,290 --> 00:30:12,130
Yeah?

536
00:30:12,250 --> 00:30:13,090
For sure.

537
00:30:13,290 --> 00:30:14,250
We should do this more often.

538
00:30:14,490 --> 00:30:15,330
Alright.

539
00:30:15,350 --> 00:30:16,200
Enjoy your meal.

540
00:30:16,210 --> 00:30:17,050
- Okay.
- Bye.

541
00:30:17,050 --> 00:30:18,310
- Bye.
- Bye.

542
00:30:20,900 --> 00:30:22,770
Honey, are you alright?

543
00:30:23,010 --> 00:30:24,050
You look a bit pale.

544
00:30:24,730 --> 00:30:25,570
I'm fine.

545
00:30:34,220 --> 00:30:36,180
Are you sure you don't want me
to drive you home?

546
00:30:37,250 --> 00:30:38,090
No need.

547
00:30:38,380 --> 00:30:39,250
I want to take the subway

548
00:30:39,860 --> 00:30:40,860
and walk a bit.

549
00:30:42,770 --> 00:30:45,010
With so much stuff,
the subway won't be convenient.

550
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:46,300
Let me drive you.

551
00:30:47,330 --> 00:30:49,180
These two big bags are for you.

552
00:30:50,940 --> 00:30:52,380
All this is for me?

553
00:30:52,380 --> 00:30:53,220
Yeah.

554
00:30:53,570 --> 00:30:56,460
I want your fridge always be full.

555
00:30:58,460 --> 00:30:59,380
So thoughtful?

556
00:31:01,290 --> 00:31:02,140
Sorry about that.

557
00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:09,460
Is it that same annoying person again?

558
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:12,220
Yeah.

559
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:14,530
Let's sit over there for a bit.

560
00:31:14,860 --> 00:31:15,700
Okay.

561
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:24,570
You bought so much stuff.

562
00:31:25,140 --> 00:31:25,980
Just now,

563
00:31:26,330 --> 00:31:27,170
I thought

564
00:31:27,330 --> 00:31:28,570
it was for you.

565
00:31:30,460 --> 00:31:32,980
If you get hungry, heat up a pizza.

566
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,020
Also,

567
00:31:35,530 --> 00:31:36,770
there are some deluxe soup wontons.

568
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:38,260
And this one,

569
00:31:40,220 --> 00:31:41,060
mushroom rice.

570
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:44,090
Anyway, stop eating instant noodles
all the time, okay?

571
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:45,820
I'll listen to you.

572
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:55,700
This feels so good.

573
00:31:57,010 --> 00:31:58,050
Yeah, it really does.

574
00:32:01,730 --> 00:32:02,700
Hey,

575
00:32:03,290 --> 00:32:05,380
will Yu He really join our gathering?

576
00:32:08,660 --> 00:32:09,660
No idea.

577
00:32:10,050 --> 00:32:11,050
But I can see

578
00:32:11,530 --> 00:32:12,660
she still cares about Gong.

579
00:32:13,420 --> 00:32:15,220
I think she still hasn't moved on.

580
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:17,660
You noticed that, too?

581
00:32:18,570 --> 00:32:19,410
Of course.

582
00:32:20,570 --> 00:32:22,940
Seems women hold on more.

583
00:32:24,570 --> 00:32:25,530
Not necessarily.

584
00:32:26,050 --> 00:32:28,090
If we ever broke up someday,

585
00:32:28,460 --> 00:32:30,140
I think I'd be the one
who couldn't move on.

586
00:32:30,530 --> 00:32:31,490
No ifs.

587
00:32:32,460 --> 00:32:33,420
I won't allow it.

588
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:37,010
Then remember what you said.

589
00:32:37,620 --> 00:32:38,460
Pinky swear.

590
00:32:40,460 --> 00:32:41,330
Pinky swear.

591
00:32:41,330 --> 00:32:44,420
Pinky swear,
can't break it for a hundred years.

592
00:32:44,770 --> 00:32:46,140
Alright, remember your words.

593
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:47,490
You have to remember.

594
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:49,530
- Yeah?
- You're so childish.

595
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:53,090
Anyway, you promised not to break up.

596
00:32:53,250 --> 00:32:54,090
Okay.

597
00:32:56,180 --> 00:32:57,810
Look at that bridge. It's so beautiful.

598
00:32:58,220 --> 00:32:59,060
Yeah.

599
00:33:20,260 --> 00:33:24,900
(Voice call)

600
00:33:25,620 --> 00:33:27,250
(Are you busy? Let's meet tonight.)

601
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:29,220
(Done with work? I've got something.)

602
00:33:35,100 --> 00:33:37,060
(Let's talk another day...)

603
00:33:43,060 --> 00:33:45,180
(What's it about...?)

604
00:33:51,340 --> 00:33:54,260
(Coming...)

605
00:33:54,620 --> 00:33:55,460
(Coming.)

606
00:34:03,570 --> 00:34:04,620
(I heard people say)

607
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:06,700
(that after someone achieves
fame and success,)

608
00:34:06,940 --> 00:34:08,380
(the first thing they want to do)

609
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:10,380
(is erase those)

610
00:34:10,780 --> 00:34:11,620
(who know their past.)

611
00:34:12,900 --> 00:34:14,170
(I'm starting to worry)

612
00:34:14,530 --> 00:34:17,460
(about who's holding
the sword of Damocles over me.)

613
00:34:26,420 --> 00:34:28,340
(I'm starting to fear)

614
00:34:28,650 --> 00:34:30,300
(the unintentional crossing
of gazes in crowds.)

615
00:34:30,740 --> 00:34:32,780
(I'm afraid someone might recognize me)

616
00:34:33,210 --> 00:34:34,690
(and expose my past.)

617
00:34:45,170 --> 00:34:46,530
(Bei)
(I'm home, and you?)

618
00:34:46,530 --> 00:34:47,480
(Xiaoxi)
(Almost there.)

619
00:34:48,420 --> 00:34:49,530
Bad woman.

620
00:34:49,980 --> 00:34:51,010
Bad woman...

621
00:34:51,570 --> 00:34:52,690
Bad woman.

622
00:34:53,610 --> 00:34:54,450
You bad woman.

623
00:34:58,300 --> 00:35:00,210
Doing things like that
will come back to you.

624
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:03,820
It will come back to you.

625
00:35:04,090 --> 00:35:04,980
You'll pay for that.

626
00:35:04,980 --> 00:35:05,820
Bad woman.

627
00:35:05,940 --> 00:35:06,940
Heaven will strike you down.

628
00:35:07,490 --> 00:35:08,610
You bad woman.

629
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:10,170
You broke up someone's family.

630
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:29,540
(Wild & Proud Rose)

631
00:35:32,980 --> 00:35:34,380
Xiaoxi, it's been a while.

632
00:35:34,980 --> 00:35:35,860
Is Ms. Guan in?

633
00:35:36,050 --> 00:35:37,410
She's in the reception room
waiting for you.

634
00:35:37,420 --> 00:35:38,260
I'll take you over.

635
00:35:38,420 --> 00:35:39,610
No need, I'll go myself.

636
00:35:39,610 --> 00:35:40,450
Alright.

637
00:36:00,210 --> 00:36:02,210
Xiaoxi, come in.

638
00:36:08,490 --> 00:36:09,330
Guan.

639
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:12,530
A few days ago,

640
00:36:13,570 --> 00:36:16,260
I was chatting
with some friends over tea.

641
00:36:17,010 --> 00:36:17,940
We talked about my ex-husband.

642
00:36:19,490 --> 00:36:21,650
They said that since we split up,

643
00:36:22,820 --> 00:36:23,900
my condition

644
00:36:24,740 --> 00:36:25,820
has gotten better and better.

645
00:36:27,690 --> 00:36:28,780
Why bring this up?

646
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:30,100
Lately,

647
00:36:30,260 --> 00:36:31,380
I keep thinking about the past.

648
00:36:32,650 --> 00:36:33,490
Thankfully,

649
00:36:34,380 --> 00:36:35,610
I met you.

650
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:38,340
You helped me a lot.

651
00:36:44,210 --> 00:36:45,050
They said

652
00:36:45,740 --> 00:36:46,900
our birth charts match.

653
00:36:47,460 --> 00:36:48,300
We're each other's

654
00:36:48,650 --> 00:36:49,490
lucky stars.

655
00:36:52,530 --> 00:36:53,370
I don't believe that.

656
00:36:54,570 --> 00:36:55,410
Neither do I.

657
00:36:56,860 --> 00:36:57,700
Have a seat.

658
00:36:58,860 --> 00:36:59,940
But I do believe

659
00:37:00,340 --> 00:37:01,460
in fate between people.

660
00:37:02,340 --> 00:37:03,490
Look how smoothly

661
00:37:03,650 --> 00:37:04,780
we've worked together.

662
00:37:06,650 --> 00:37:07,820
I've always been grateful

663
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:09,570
for your trust in me.

664
00:37:12,780 --> 00:37:14,900
Why haven't you come lately?

665
00:37:16,980 --> 00:37:17,900
I've been swamped recently.

666
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:20,490
You've got it easy, huh?

667
00:37:21,210 --> 00:37:22,940
Lots of people came
because of your name.

668
00:37:23,490 --> 00:37:24,570
But you pulled a disappearing act,

669
00:37:25,050 --> 00:37:26,260
making it tough for us.

670
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:33,300
You could've just told them that I quit.

671
00:37:34,900 --> 00:37:37,900
Back then, you swore that

672
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:40,340
you'd help all women

673
00:37:40,610 --> 00:37:42,130
see through scumbags.

674
00:37:42,870 --> 00:37:46,050
You said those unfaithful men
don't deserve love.

675
00:37:47,050 --> 00:37:48,090
Where's that fearless,

676
00:37:48,090 --> 00:37:49,690
righteous Xiaoxi we used to know?

677
00:37:53,570 --> 00:37:54,940
Lately, I've been thinking,

678
00:37:58,820 --> 00:38:00,380
can love really be authenticated?

679
00:38:01,260 --> 00:38:02,340
Have you forgotten

680
00:38:02,690 --> 00:38:03,980
those men

681
00:38:04,170 --> 00:38:05,740
who cheat behind their partners' backs

682
00:38:06,900 --> 00:38:07,740
and flirt with you?

683
00:38:08,010 --> 00:38:09,300
Then what am I doing?

684
00:38:11,570 --> 00:38:13,130
Pushing men to their limits,

685
00:38:13,460 --> 00:38:15,300
creating false accusations,

686
00:38:15,650 --> 00:38:16,860
then leaving women hopeless?

687
00:38:20,420 --> 00:38:21,740
I've broken up too many people.

688
00:38:23,740 --> 00:38:24,690
I don't want to do it anymore.

689
00:38:26,820 --> 00:38:29,130
Who planted that idea in your head?

690
00:38:30,460 --> 00:38:33,010
I asked you here

691
00:38:33,260 --> 00:38:34,210
because I need your help.

692
00:38:35,300 --> 00:38:37,610
A few friends insist on meeting you.

693
00:38:38,130 --> 00:38:39,300
It's tough for me.

694
00:38:41,010 --> 00:38:42,090
Please, don't make it hard for me.

695
00:38:44,260 --> 00:38:45,100
Alright.

696
00:38:46,420 --> 00:38:48,340
I won't pressure you, I won't.

697
00:38:50,210 --> 00:38:52,420
Hey, heard you've got a boyfriend.

698
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:11,130
Nothing escapes you, huh?

699
00:39:12,530 --> 00:39:14,210
I've been in business for years.

700
00:39:14,690 --> 00:39:15,530
I've got plenty of friends.

701
00:39:17,050 --> 00:39:17,890
Another day,

702
00:39:18,170 --> 00:39:20,130
bring your boyfriend over for a meal.

703
00:39:21,260 --> 00:39:22,570
The man you picked

704
00:39:22,940 --> 00:39:25,050
must be loyal, right?

705
00:39:27,380 --> 00:39:28,220
Sure.

706
00:39:28,490 --> 00:39:29,570
We'll come when there's a chance.

707
00:39:33,010 --> 00:39:34,170
About that thing you mentioned,

708
00:39:34,170 --> 00:39:35,780
give me some time to think it over.

709
00:39:37,980 --> 00:39:38,820
Alright.

710
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:39,850
I'll wait.

711
00:39:53,001 --> 00:39:55,600
♪I'll admit♪

712
00:39:55,601 --> 00:39:59,640
♪My back is faced against the wall♪

713
00:40:00,521 --> 00:40:04,387
♪There's nothing that I wouldn't try to do♪

714
00:40:04,412 --> 00:40:08,600
♪For this feeling to have you♪

715
00:40:08,881 --> 00:40:11,080
♪I'll resist♪

716
00:40:11,401 --> 00:40:13,415
♪Your gaze, your lips♪

717
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:15,600
♪Your touches again♪

718
00:40:16,481 --> 00:40:20,461
♪There's no one that
I wouldn't try to fool♪

719
00:40:20,486 --> 00:40:23,520
♪For an image of you♪

720
00:40:24,521 --> 00:40:26,960
♪Take my hand again♪

721
00:40:26,961 --> 00:40:28,720
♪Take my mind again♪

722
00:40:28,801 --> 00:40:32,160
♪Break into my heart again♪

723
00:40:32,561 --> 00:40:34,738
♪I'm falling out again♪

724
00:40:34,763 --> 00:40:36,600
♪I'm on my knees again♪

725
00:40:36,601 --> 00:40:40,440
♪To beg for the truth♪

726
00:40:42,281 --> 00:40:46,440
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

727
00:40:46,441 --> 00:40:51,440
♪Is that the secret to love♪

728
00:40:51,801 --> 00:40:54,760
♪I thought it had came from below us♪

729
00:40:54,841 --> 00:40:58,240
♪Did it come from above♪

730
00:40:58,321 --> 00:41:02,080
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

731
00:41:02,321 --> 00:41:07,400
♪Is that the secret to love♪

732
00:41:07,801 --> 00:41:10,240
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing,♪

733
00:41:10,241 --> 00:41:14,680
♪this secret of love♪
